channel.title: Runescape world subdomains?
channel.description:
im making a world switcher client in visual basic for my clan and need a list of the subdomains for each world coz finding them 1 by 1 by checking each world would be very time consuming, i saw a thread before about something like the ultimate pker client and a guy had posted just this, all help appreciated.
Oh also, just so i dont have to experiment around myself, what are the options at the end of the url that specify java version and detail etc... thank you.
EDIT: ok ive found most of the parameters for the url, L=low mem or not, P=Java Plugin, i dont know what the j parameter does, i've tried several combinations of detail and plugin and it always is set to 1.....

item.title: Runescape world subdomains?
item.dc:creator: @The_Un-Named The Un-Named
item.description:
@The_Un-Named wrote:

puref0rlyfe:

EDIT: ok ive found most of the parameters for the url, L=low mem or not, P=Java Plugin, i dont know what the j parameter does, i’ve tried several combinations of detail and plugin and it always is set to 1…

l0 is high detail, l1 is low detail. p0 is signed using default java, p1 is signed using sun java and p2 is unsigned using default java. j, I don’t know what it means either, I will have a look when I get home though.

How could I be so stupid? j means javascript, because if javascript is enabled, you can’t directly load the page(it redirects to the homepage), but I believe it loads the game in javascript, when it’s disabled(j0), it uses the usual html methods.

For the subdomains(eg, ul8(world 2)), use this program: www.freddy1990.com/fawg.php
